abstract: A federal court ruled that President Trump’s proclamation of a national emergency did not justify tapping into Pentagon construction funds.
snippet: A federal court ruled that President Trump’s proclamation of a national emergency did not justify tapping into Pentagon construction funds.
lead_paragraph: A federal court in Texas issued a nationwide injunction late on Tuesday preventing the Trump administration from using $3.6 billion in military construction funds to erect a wall along the southern border, ruling that an emergency proclamation that enabled the government to access the funds was unlawful.

abstract: President Recep Tayyip Erdogan said Turkey might send troops to Libya to counter Russian-backed militia forces.
snippet: President Recep Tayyip Erdogan said Turkey might send troops to Libya to counter Russian-backed militia forces.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — The battle for control of Libya threatened to escalate further this week as Turkey said it might intervene to stop the Russian-backed forces now closing in on Tripoli, the capital.

abstract: President Donald Trump will sign an executive order on Wednesday targeting antisemitism on college campuses, the White House said.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump will sign an executive order on Wednesday targeting antisemitism on college campuses, the White House said.
headline_main: Trump to Sign Order Targeting Anti-Semitism at Colleges
headline_print_headline: Trump to Sign Order Targeting Anti-Semitism at Colleges

abstract: The latest effort to rework a program for borrowers whose schools broke the law drew an immediate promise of a court challenge.
snippet: The latest effort to rework a program for borrowers whose schools broke the law drew an immediate promise of a court challenge.
lead_paragraph: Thousands of students who took out federal loans to attend schools that lured them with fraudulent claims will still have to repay a portion of their debts, the Education Department said Tuesday — a new attempt to water down a loan-forgiveness program that the department’s leader has long deplored.

abstract: For the House progressives:  a pair of impeachment articles against President Donald Trump. For the vulnerable Democratic freshmen: charges that are narrowly focused on Ukraine. And for the whole House Democratic majority — and, however backhandedly, Trump himself: a sweeping new trade deal.
snippet: For the House progressives:  a pair of impeachment articles against President Donald Trump. For the vulnerable Democratic freshmen: charges that are narrowly focused on Ukraine. And for the whole House Democratic majority — and, however backhanded...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — For the House progressives: a pair of impeachment articles against President Donald Trump. For the vulnerable Democratic freshmen: charges that are narrowly focused on Ukraine. And for the whole House Democratic majority — and, however backhandedly, Trump himself: a sweeping new trade deal.
headline_main: Pelosi Offers Some Trade Policy With That Impeachment
headline_print_headline: Pelosi Offers Some Trade Policy With That Impeachment

abstract: How does Trump’s attorney general keep a straight face?
snippet: How does Trump’s attorney general keep a straight face?
lead_paragraph: Donald Trump famously said that he could shoot somebody in the middle of Fifth Avenue and not “lose any voters.” I don’t know about that. But I’m confident that he wouldn’t lose Bill Barr.

abstract: Rudy Giuliani, President Donald Trump’s personal attorney, said Tuesday that the president asked him to brief the Justice Department and Republican senators on the findings of his recent trip to Ukraine.
snippet: Rudy Giuliani, President Donald Trump’s personal attorney, said Tuesday that the president asked him to brief the Justice Department and Republican senators on the findings of his recent trip to Ukraine.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Rudy Giuliani, President Donald Trump’s personal attorney, said Tuesday that the president asked him to brief the Justice Department and Republican senators on the findings of his recent trip to Ukraine.
headline_main: Giuliani Indicates He'll Report on Ukraine Trip This Week
headline_print_headline: Giuliani Indicates He'll Report on Ukraine Trip This Week

abstract: U.S. Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell raised the prospect on Tuesday of a short Senate impeachment trial for President Donald Trump in which no witnesses would be called.
snippet: U.S. Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell raised the prospect on Tuesday of a short Senate impeachment trial for President Donald Trump in which no witnesses would be called.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell raised the prospect on Tuesday of a short Senate impeachment trial for President Donald Trump in which no witnesses would be called.
headline_main: U.S. Senate Leader McConnell Raises Possibility of Quick Impeachment Trial
headline_print_headline: U.S. Senate Leader McConnell Raises Possibility of Quick Impeachment Trial
